From Kalki Dasa Subject Bhagavad Gita TEXT bhogaisvarya prasaktanam tayapahrta cetasam vyavasayatmika buddhih samadhau na vidhiyate bhoga to material enjoyment aisvarya and opulence prasaktanam for those who are attached taya by such things apahrta cetasam bewildered in mind vyavasaya atmika fixed in determination buddhih devotional service to the Lord samadhau in the controlled mind na never vidhiyate does take TRANSLATION In the minds of those who are too attached to sense enjoyment and material opulence and who are bewildered by such things the resolute determination for devotional service to the Supreme Lord does not take PURPORT Samadhi means fixed '' The Vedic dictionary the Nirukti says samyag adhiyate 'sminn atma tattva yathatmyam When the mind is fixed for understanding the self it is said to be in '' Samadhi is never possible for persons interested in material sense enjoyment nor for those who are bewildered by such temporary They are more or less condemned by the process of material Bhagavad Gita As It Is Books of Bhaktivedanta Swami Don't forget to chant Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare Kalki's Infoline BBS Aiken South Carolina USA